==English==
===Etymology===
Latin [[septentrionalis]], from [[septentriones]] (originally ''[[septem]] [[triones]]''), the seven stars of the Great Bear, from [[septem]] ‘seven’ + [[triones]] (plural of [[trio#Latin|trio]] ‘plough-ox’).

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /sɛp'tɛntrɪənəl/

